abstracts.cdata!:
The proposed project consists of the
            rehabilitation of 6,830 feet of existing sea defense
            structures and the construction of 1,570 feet of new
            structures, construction of a diversion road, construction
            of eight drainage outfalls, construction of a slipway,
            procurement of two tugs and nine pontoons, purchase of steel
            sheet piles and equipment, consultant services for the
            detailed engineering and supervision of construction.
